Hmmm....I'm not sure I understand. I need a little help sometimes. Can you say it in a different way? I understand the best when people ask me short questions or tell me one thing at a time instead of "the whole story."

For example, you can ask me "What are the hours?" and I will understand, but if you say "My landlord is trying to evict me. I am so glad your services are free. What hours are you open?" I may get confused and not know what to say.

I will try my best to help!
